Here are a few crisp ways to introduce yourself as Lead Analyst – Artificial Intelligence (pick based on audience). I’ll keep them short, confident, and “AI LAB” aligned.

Option 1 (clean + professional, 10 seconds)

“Hi everyone, I’m [Your Name], Lead Analyst – Artificial Intelligence at Coforge AI LAB. I work on applied AI initiatives, especially building enterprise-ready AI solutions that improve delivery and governance.”

Option 2 (more specific to your topic, 10–12 seconds)

“Hi, I’m [Your Name], Lead Analyst – Artificial Intelligence in Coforge AI LAB. I focus on practical AI for software engineering—how we can use coding agents safely, consistently, and at enterprise scale.”

Option 3 (leadership-friendly, outcome framing, 12–15 seconds)

“Hello, I’m [Your Name], Lead Analyst – AI at Coforge AI LAB. My role is to translate AI capabilities into enterprise impact—productivity, quality, and governance—without adding risk.”

Option 4 (more technical, for dev teams, 10–12 seconds)

“Hey, I’m [Your Name], Lead Analyst – AI with Coforge AI LAB. I build and evaluate agentic workflows—templates, tool orchestration, and design-to-code automation—to make AI-assisted development reliable.”

Option 5 (very short, 5–7 seconds)

“Hi, I’m [Your Name], Lead Analyst – Artificial Intelligence at Coforge AI LAB.”
